00:46:37,914 --> 00:46:40,882
He won't say.
Apparently, they didn't win.

755
00:46:41,284 --> 00:46:42,478
So you see.

756
00:46:42,585 --> 00:46:46,920
We are artist, pirate.
More than cooks are we.

757
00:46:47,023 --> 00:46:50,423
- We?
- Oui. You are one of us now, oui?

758
00:46:50,726 --> 00:46:55,255
Oui. Thank you, by the way,
for all the advice about cooking.

759
00:46:55,632 --> 00:46:58,099
- Thank you, too.
- For what?

760
00:46:58,335 --> 00:46:59,802
For taking it.

761
00:47:00,170 --> 00:47:01,603
(MUSIC PLA YIN G ON RADIO)

762
00:47:02,505 --> 00:47:03,802
Huh?

763
00:47:04,541 --> 00:47:05,735
The rat!

764
00:47:07,943 --> 00:47:10,969
- (STUTTERING) But he is a...
- (TITTERING) I just dropped my keys.

765
00:47:14,650 --> 00:47:16,516
Have you decided this evening?

766
00:47:16,619 --> 00:47:20,681
- Your soup is excellent. But...
- But we order it every time.

767
00:47:20,789 --> 00:47:24,351
- What else do you have?
- Well, we have a very nice foie gras.

768
00:47:24,460 --> 00:47:25,518
I know about the foie gras.

769
00:47:25,628 --> 00:47:27,425
The old standby,
used to be famous for it.

770
00:47:27,530 --> 00:47:29,657
What does the chef have that's new?

771
00:47:30,500 --> 00:47:31,489
(DOOR SLAMMING)

772
00:47:31,601 --> 00:47:33,228
- Someone has asked what is new!
- New?

773
00:47:33,335 --> 00:47:34,324
Yes. What do I tell them?

774
00:47:34,436 --> 00:47:36,132
- Well, what did you tell them?
- I told them I would ask!

775
00:47:36,239 --> 00:47:37,536
What are you blathering about?

776
00:47:37,641 --> 00:47:39,733
- Customers are asking what is new.
- What should I tell them?

777
00:47:39,842 --> 00:47:42,311
- What did you tell them?
- I told them I would ask!

778
00:47:42,646 --> 00:47:43,806
(PONDERING)

779
00:47:43,914 --> 00:47:45,244
This is simple.

780
00:47:45,347 --> 00:47:47,474
Just pull out an old Gusteau recipe,

781
00:47:47,583 --> 00:47:49,244
something we haven't made
in a while...

782
00:47:49,351 --> 00:47:53,117
They know about the old stuff.
They like Linguini's soup.

783
00:47:54,190 --> 00:47:58,820
They are asking for food from Linguini?

784
00:47:59,262 --> 00:48:01,730
A lot of customers like the soup.
That's all we are saying.

785
00:48:01,831 --> 00:48:03,389
Were we saying that?

786
00:48:04,233 --> 00:48:07,168
Very well. If it's Linguini they want

787
00:48:07,269 --> 00:48:11,831
tell them Chef Linguini has prepared
something special for them.

788
00:48:11,942 --> 00:48:15,036
Something definitely off menu.

789
00:48:15,445 --> 00:48:17,036
Oh, and don't forget to stress

790
00:48:17,146 --> 00:48:19,614
- its Linguini-ness.
- Oui, chef.

791
00:48:19,715 --> 00:48:23,880
Now is your chance to try something
worthy of your talent, Linguini.

792
00:48:23,987 --> 00:48:29,289
A forgotten favorite of the chef's,
sweetbread ŕ la Gusteau.

793
00:48:29,391 --> 00:48:31,018
- Colette will help you.
- Oui, chef.

794
00:48:31,126 --> 00:48:33,994
Now, hurry up. Our diners are hungry.

795
00:48:34,463 --> 00:48:36,898
Are you sure?
That recipe was a disaster.

796
00:48:37,000 --> 00:48:38,728
Gusteau himself said so.

797
00:48:38,835 --> 00:48:42,202
Just the sort of challenge
a budding chef needs.

798
00:48:42,539 --> 00:48:43,869
"Sweetbread ŕ la Gusteau.

799
00:48:43,974 --> 00:48:46,465
"Sweetbread cooked
in a seaweed salt crust

800
00:48:46,576 --> 00:48:49,510
"with cuttlefish tentacle,
dog rose purée,

801
00:48:49,612 --> 00:48:52,137
"geoduck egg, dried white fungus?

802
00:48:52,248 --> 00:48:55,012
"Anchovy licorice sauce."

803
00:48:55,351 --> 00:48:58,480
I don't know this recipe,
but it's Gusteau's, so...

804
00:48:58,588 --> 00:49:01,112
Lalo! We have
some veal stomach soaking, yes?

805
00:49:01,224 --> 00:49:03,215
LALO: Yes!
The veal stomach, I get that.

806
00:49:03,326 --> 00:49:04,519
Veal stomach?

807
00:49:11,967 --> 00:49:13,059
Oh!

808
00:49:13,168 --> 00:49:14,226
Okay.

809
00:49:20,175 --> 00:49:21,403
(SNIFFING)

810
00:49:22,244 --> 00:49:24,644
I'll be right back. Where...

811
00:49:26,048 --> 00:49:27,949
Hey, I got to... Hey!

812
00:49:28,284 --> 00:49:32,311
Don't mind me.
I just need to borrow this real quick.

813
00:49:32,521 --> 00:49:34,614
Let's see, over here...

814
00:49:34,724 --> 00:49:35,985
I'll be back.

815
00:49:37,159 --> 00:49:38,217
Thank you.

816
00:49:39,128 --> 00:49:40,596
Excuse me. I'm going to...

817
00:49:40,697 --> 00:49:43,291
Apparently, I need this. I'll be right...

818
00:49:43,432 --> 00:49:45,094
I'm going to pick that up.

819
00:49:45,201 --> 00:49:47,396
I got some of that spice.

820
00:49:48,304 --> 00:49:49,498
Okay.

821
00:49:49,739 --> 00:49:50,864
What are you doing? You're supposed

822
00:49:50,974 --> 00:49:52,271
to be preparing the Gusteau recipe.

823
00:49:52,375 --> 00:49:53,706
(STUTTERING)
This is the recipe.

824
00:49:53,809 --> 00:49:55,869
The recipe doesn't call
for white truffle oil!

825
00:49:55,978 --> 00:49:58,503
What else have you...
You are improvising?

826
00:49:58,614 --> 00:50:01,048
This is no time to experiment.
The customer are waiting.

827
00:50:01,150 --> 00:50:03,380
You're right. I should listen to you!

828
00:50:04,320 --> 00:50:05,684
- Stop that!
- Stop what?

829
00:50:05,789 --> 00:50:08,349
Freaking me out!
Whatever you are doing, stop it.

830
00:50:08,458 --> 00:50:10,483
- HORST: Where is the special order?
- Coming!

831
00:50:10,592 --> 00:50:12,856
- I thought we were together on this.
- We are together.

832
00:50:12,961 --> 00:50:15,623
- Then what are you doing?
- It's very hard to explain.

833
00:50:15,731 --> 00:50:18,030
- The special?
- Come get it!

834
00:50:20,135 --> 00:50:22,797
Whoa, whoa.
I forgot the anchovy licorice sauce.

835
00:50:23,773 --> 00:50:24,932
(EX CLAIMS)

836
00:50:26,108 --> 00:50:27,336
(GASPING)

837
00:50:28,110 --> 00:50:32,206
- Don't you dare.
- I'm not, I'm not. I'm...

838
00:50:35,318 --> 00:50:36,409
Sorry.

839
00:50:38,353 --> 00:50:40,914
Is Linguini's dish done yet?

840
00:50:41,023 --> 00:50:44,050
Ja. It's as bad as we remember.
Just went out.

841
00:50:44,159 --> 00:50:47,755
- Did you taste it?
- Ja, of course, before he changed it.

842
00:50:47,864 --> 00:50:50,661
Good. What? How could he change it?

843
00:50:50,766 --> 00:50:52,860
He changed it
as it was going out the door!

844
00:50:52,969 --> 00:50:53,958
Ow!

845
00:50:54,070 --> 00:50:55,036
They love it!

846
00:50:55,137 --> 00:50:57,867
Other diners are already
asking about it, about Linguini.

847
00:50:57,974 --> 00:50:59,737
I have seven more orders!

848
00:50:59,842 --> 00:51:02,471
That's wonderful.

849
00:51:07,182 --> 00:51:08,309
I'd like one of those.

850
00:51:10,853 --> 00:51:12,344
Special order!

851
00:51:16,226 --> 00:51:17,193
What is that?

852
00:51:17,293 --> 00:51:20,592
HORST: Special order! Special order!
Special order!

853
00:51:28,938 --> 00:51:30,371
ALL: To Linguini.

854
00:51:30,472 --> 00:51:33,032
- Congratulations, Mr. Linguini.
- Cheers, ja?

855
00:51:33,543 --> 00:51:35,510
LAROUSSE: Drink now, there's plenty.

856
00:51:39,882 --> 00:51:42,248
Take a break, Little Chef. Get some air.

857
00:51:43,318 --> 00:51:45,309
We really did it tonight.

858
00:51:50,193 --> 00:51:51,523
Dah!

859
00:51:52,262 --> 00:51:53,626
(GRUNTS)

860
00:51:55,264 --> 00:51:56,856
(CHUCKLES) Got your toque!

861
00:51:57,867 --> 00:51:59,231
Oh, seriously now.

862
00:51:59,434 --> 00:52:04,065
I'd love to have a little talk with you,
Linguini, in my office.

863
00:52:04,173 --> 00:52:06,835
- Am I in trouble?
- Trouble? No.

864
00:52:06,943 --> 00:52:10,742
A little wine, a friendly chat.
Just us cooks.

865
00:52:10,847 --> 00:52:12,246
(CHUCKLING GRACIOUSLY)

866
00:52:12,347 --> 00:52:15,840
The plongeur won't be coming to you
for advice anymore, eh, Colette?

867
00:52:15,952 --> 00:52:18,681
He's gotten all he needs.

868
00:52:18,788 --> 00:52:20,085
(SNICKERING)

869
00:52:21,456 --> 00:52:24,324
Toasting your success, eh, Linguini?

870
00:52:25,827 --> 00:52:27,351
Good for you.

871
00:52:27,463 --> 00:52:31,456
I just took it to be polite.
I don't really drink, you know.

872
00:52:31,568 --> 00:52:35,664
Of course you don't.
I wouldn't either if I was drinking that.

873
00:52:35,771 --> 00:52:39,969
But you would have to be an idiot
of elephantine proportions

874
00:52:40,076 --> 00:52:44,103
not to appreciate
this '61 Château Latour.

875
00:52:44,313 --> 00:52:48,375
And you, Monsieur Linguini,
are no idiot.

876
00:52:49,318 --> 00:52:52,186
Let us toast your non-idiocy.

877
00:52:59,829 --> 00:53:01,126
(SLURPING)

878
00:53:04,166 --> 00:53:05,599
(CLATTERING)

879
00:53:16,012 --> 00:53:17,876
- Remy!
- Emile?

880
00:53:18,248 --> 00:53:20,112
I can't believe it! You're alive!

881
00:53:20,215 --> 00:53:21,773
- You made it!
- I thought I'd never see you guys again!

882
00:53:21,884 --> 00:53:23,818
We figured
you didn't survive the rapids.

883
00:53:23,920 --> 00:53:26,081
And what are you eating?

884
00:53:28,958 --> 00:53:30,721
I don't really know.

885
00:53:30,827 --> 00:53:34,023
I think it was
some sort of wrapper once.

886
00:53:34,130 --> 00:53:38,829
What? No.
You're in Paris now, baby. My town.

887
00:53:38,934 --> 00:53:42,427
No brother of mine eats rejectamenta
in my town.

888
00:53:44,539 --> 00:53:46,097
(PEOPLE LAUGHING)

889
00:53:49,711 --> 00:53:50,871
(GRUNTING)

890
00:53:51,947 --> 00:53:55,315
Remy! You are stealing?
You told Linguini he could trust you.

891
00:53:55,418 --> 00:53:59,684
- And he can. It's for my brother.
- But the boy could lose his job.

892
00:53:59,789 --> 00:54:02,952
Which means I would, too.
It's under control, okay?

893
00:54:03,860 --> 00:54:07,818
- More wine?
- I shouldn't, but... Okay.

894
00:54:08,197 --> 00:54:11,530
So, where did you train, Linguini?

895
00:54:11,634 --> 00:54:13,931
Train? All right.

896
00:54:14,170 --> 00:54:18,664
Surely you don't expect me to believe
this is your first time cooking?

897
00:54:18,775 --> 00:54:20,106
- It's not.
- I knew it!

898
00:54:20,208 --> 00:54:23,940
It's my... Second, third, fourth...
Fifth time.

899
00:54:24,047 --> 00:54:25,639
Monday was my first time.

900
00:54:25,748 --> 00:54:28,512
But I've taken out the garbage
lots of times before that...

901
00:54:28,617 --> 00:54:30,882
Yes, yes. Have some more wine.

902
00:54:31,019 --> 00:54:34,217
Tell me, Linguini, about your interests.

903
00:54:34,324 --> 00:54:36,349
Do you like animals?

904
00:54:36,458 --> 00:54:39,188
(CHUCKLING) What?
Animals? What kind?

905
00:54:40,028 --> 00:54:43,829
The usual, dogs, cats, horses,
guinea pigs,

906
00:54:43,932 --> 00:54:45,092
rats.

907
00:54:46,601 --> 00:54:47,693
I brought you something to...

908
00:54:47,804 --> 00:54:48,771
(SCREAMS)

909
00:54:48,871 --> 00:54:49,894
No, no, no, no!

910
00:54:50,005 --> 00:54:51,666
Spit that out right now!

911
00:54:52,608 --> 00:54:55,735
I have got to teach you about food.
Close your eyes.

912
00:54:56,244 --> 00:55:00,648
Now take a bite of... No! No! No!

913
00:55:00,782 --> 00:55:04,150
- Don't just hork it down!
- Too late.

914
00:55:04,387 --> 00:55:05,648
Here.

915
00:55:05,954 --> 00:55:10,324
Chew it slowly.
Only think about the taste.

916
00:55:12,862 --> 00:55:14,887
- See?
- Not really.

917
00:55:14,996 --> 00:55:18,228
Creamy, salty sweet,
an oaky nuttiness.

918
00:55:18,333 --> 00:55:21,360
- You detect that?
- Oh, I'm detecting nuttiness.

919
00:55:21,471 --> 00:55:24,565
Close your eyes. Now taste this.

920
00:55:25,041 --> 00:55:30,103
Whole different thing, right?
Sweet, crisp, slight tang on the finish.

921
00:55:30,213 --> 00:55:33,807
- Okay.
- Now, try them together.

922
00:55:34,751 --> 00:55:35,911
Okay.

923
00:55:36,385 --> 00:55:39,844
I think I'm getting
a little something there.

924
00:55:40,056 --> 00:55:42,047
- It might be the nuttiness.
- See?

925
00:55:42,157 --> 00:55:43,887
- Could be the tang.
- That's it.

926
00:55:43,992 --> 00:55:45,824
Now, imagine every great taste
in the world

927
00:55:45,927 --> 00:55:47,896
being combined
into infinite combinations.

928
00:55:47,996 --> 00:55:51,056
Tastes that no one has tried yet!
Discoveries to be made!

929
00:55:51,166 --> 00:55:52,532
I think...

930
00:55:53,702 --> 00:55:56,228
- You lost me again.
- (GROANING) Yeah.

931
00:55:56,338 --> 00:55:57,806
But that was interesting.

932
00:55:57,907 --> 00:56:00,670
Most interesting garbage I ever...
Hey! What are we doing?

933
00:56:00,777 --> 00:56:02,141
Dad doesn't know you're alive yet!

934
00:56:02,244 --> 00:56:04,543
We've got to go to the colony!
Everyone will be thrilled!

935
00:56:04,646 --> 00:56:06,204
- Yeah! But...
- What?

936
00:56:06,315 --> 00:56:09,250
Thing is, I kind of have to...

937
00:56:09,786 --> 00:56:11,777
What do you "have to"
more than family?

938
00:56:11,887 --> 00:56:13,184
What's more important here?

939
00:56:13,289 --> 00:56:14,880
Well, I...

940
00:56:16,358 --> 00:56:18,349
It wouldn't hurt to visit.

941
00:56:18,628 --> 00:56:20,289
- Have you had a pet rat?
- No.

942
00:56:20,396 --> 00:56:22,260
- Did you work in a lab with rats?
- No.

943
00:56:22,364 --> 00:56:23,855
Perhaps you lived in squalor
at some point?

944
00:56:23,965 --> 00:56:25,557
Nopety nopety no.

945
00:56:25,668 --> 00:56:28,329
You know something about rats!
You know you do!

946
00:56:28,438 --> 00:56:31,771
You know who know do whacka-doo.
Ratta-tatta.

947
00:56:31,873 --> 00:56:34,273
- Hey! Why do they call it that?
- What?

948
00:56:34,376 --> 00:56:38,472
Ratatouille. It's like a stew, right?
Why do they call it that?

949
00:56:38,815 --> 00:56:40,146
If you're going to name a food,

950
00:56:40,248 --> 00:56:43,184
you should give it a name
that sounds delicious.

951
00:56:43,318 --> 00:56:48,552
Ratatouille doesn't sound delicious.
It sounds like "rat" and "patootie."

952
00:56:48,724 --> 00:56:52,887
Rat patootie.
Which does not sound delicious.

953
00:56:54,896 --> 00:57:00,268
Regrettably we are all out of wine.

954
00:57:03,139 --> 00:57:05,106
My son has returned!

955
00:57:05,208 --> 00:57:06,766
(ALL CHEERING)

956
00:57:28,998 --> 00:57:34,594
And finding someone to replace you
for poison checker has been a disaster.

957
00:57:34,704 --> 00:57:38,538
Nothing's been poisoned, thank God,
but it hasn't been easy.

958
00:57:38,740 --> 00:57:43,143
- You didn't make it easy.
- I know. I am sorry, Dad.

959
00:57:43,246 --> 00:57:46,773
Well, the important thing
is that you're home.

960
00:57:46,882 --> 00:57:49,943
(STUTTERING) Yeah, well, about that...

961
00:57:50,052 --> 00:57:51,849
You look thin. Why is that?

962
00:57:51,954 --> 00:57:55,445
A shortage of food,
or a surplus of snobbery?

963
00:57:58,126 --> 00:58:01,152
It's tough out there in the big world
all alone, isn't it?

964
00:58:01,264 --> 00:58:04,324
Sure, but it's not like I'm a kid anymore.

965
00:58:04,432 --> 00:58:07,094
- Hey. Hey, boy. What's up?
- I can take care of myself.

966
00:58:07,202 --> 00:58:11,036
I've found a nice spot not far away,
so I'll be able to visit often.

967
00:58:11,239 --> 00:58:14,675
Nothing like a cold splash of reality
to make you...

968
00:58:14,777 --> 00:58:17,574
- Visit?
- I will. I promise. Often.

969
00:58:17,679 --> 00:58:22,617
- You're not staying?
- No. It's not a big deal, Dad. I just...

970
00:58:22,717 --> 00:58:25,346
You didn't think
I was going to stay forever, did you?

971
00:58:25,454 --> 00:58:27,684
Eventually,
a bird's got to leave the nest.

972
00:58:27,789 --> 00:58:30,054
We're not birds. We're rats.

973
00:58:30,159 --> 00:58:33,094
We don't leave our nests.
We make them bigger.

974
00:58:33,195 --> 00:58:36,186
- Well, maybe I'm a different kind of rat.
- Maybe you're not a rat at all.

975
00:58:36,298 --> 00:58:37,322
Maybe that's a good thing.

976
00:58:37,432 --> 00:58:39,867
Hey! The band's
really on tonight, huh?

977
00:58:39,969 --> 00:58:42,199
Rats. All we do is take, Dad.

978
00:58:42,304 --> 00:58:44,795
I'm tired of taking.
I want to make things.

979
00:58:44,907 --> 00:58:46,965
I want to add something to this world.

980
00:58:47,076 --> 00:58:50,170
- You're talking like a human.
- Who are not as bad as you say.

981
00:58:50,278 --> 00:58:52,940
- Oh, yeah? What makes you so sure?
- Oh, man.

982
00:58:53,048 --> 00:58:56,746
(HESITANTLY) I've been able to
observe them

983
00:58:56,851 --> 00:58:59,786
at a close-ish sort of range.

984
00:58:59,889 --> 00:59:02,152
- Yeah? How close?
- Close enough.

985
00:59:02,257 --> 00:59:05,887
And they're, you know,
not so bad as you say they are.

986
00:59:07,262 --> 00:59:10,322
Come with me.
I got something I want you to see.

987
00:59:11,934 --> 00:59:14,367
You know, I'm going to stay here.

988
00:59:15,137 --> 00:59:18,628
Make sure the floors and countertops
are clean before you lock up.

989
00:59:18,740 --> 00:59:21,903
Wait. You want me to stay and clean?

990
00:59:22,010 --> 00:59:23,911
Is that a problem?

991
00:59:24,146 --> 00:59:27,706
- No.
- Good boy. See you tomorrow.

992
00:59:31,219 --> 00:59:32,481
(SIGHING)

993
00:59:35,224 --> 00:59:36,418
We're here.

994
00:59:43,199 --> 00:59:44,358
(GASPING)

995
00:59:46,635 --> 00:59:49,103
Take a good long look, Remy.

996
00:59:50,739 --> 00:59:51,900
Now, this is what happens

997
00:59:52,007 --> 00:59:55,534
when a rat gets
a little too comfortable around humans.

998
00:59:56,512 --> 00:59:59,969
The world we live in
belongs to the enemy.

999
01:00:01,217 --> 01:00:03,344
We must live carefully.

1000
01:00:04,786 --> 01:00:07,516
We look out for our own kind, Remy.

1001
01:00:08,023 --> 01:00:11,619
When all is said and done,
we're all we've got.

1002
01:00:16,498 --> 01:00:18,898
- No.
- What?

1003
01:00:19,702 --> 01:00:25,902
No. Dad, I don't believe it.
You're telling me that the future is...

1004
01:00:26,108 --> 01:00:29,077
Can only be more of this?

1005
01:00:29,277 --> 01:00:34,476
This is the way things are.
You can't change nature.

1006
01:00:34,684 --> 01:00:39,849
Change is nature, Dad.
The part that we can influence.

1007
01:00:40,289 --> 01:00:43,485
And it starts when we decide.

1008
01:00:44,092 --> 01:00:48,324
- Where you going?
- With luck, forward.

1009
01:01:12,221 --> 01:01:13,585
Hey! Yeah.

1010
01:01:32,208 --> 01:01:33,641
(SNORING)

1011
01:01:38,313 --> 01:01:41,715
(SNORING)

1012
01:01:42,284 --> 01:01:44,114
(VEHICLE ARRIVING)

1013
01:01:53,329 --> 01:01:54,795
(MOANING)

1014
01:02:03,172 --> 01:02:04,400
(LINGUINI MOANS)

1015
01:02:11,679 --> 01:02:12,840
(SLEEPILY) Stop it.

1016
01:02:20,755 --> 01:02:22,086
(RATTLING OUTSIDE)

1017
01:02:41,744 --> 01:02:42,972
(DEEP BREATH)

1018
01:02:47,215 --> 01:02:48,443
Good morning.

1019
01:02:49,552 --> 01:02:50,541
(CLEARING THROAT)

1020
01:02:50,652 --> 01:02:52,119
Good morning.

1021
01:02:53,389 --> 01:02:57,688
So, the chef,
he invited you in for a drink?

1022
01:02:57,793 --> 01:02:59,317
That's big.

1023
01:02:59,427 --> 01:03:02,226
That's big. What did he say?

1024
01:03:06,768 --> 01:03:07,735
What?

1025
01:03:08,670 --> 01:03:10,331
What, you can't tell me?

1026
01:03:11,072 --> 01:03:12,300
Oh!

1027
01:03:12,407 --> 01:03:17,106
Forgive me for intruding on your deep,
personal relationship with the chef.

1028
01:03:17,213 --> 01:03:18,577
Oh, I see how it is.

1029
01:03:18,681 --> 01:03:21,309
You get me to teach you
a few kitchen tricks

1030
01:03:21,416 --> 01:03:24,146
to dazzle the boss
and then you blow past me?

1031
01:03:24,253 --> 01:03:25,719
Wake up. Wake up.

1032
01:03:27,056 --> 01:03:29,820
I thought you were different.

1033
01:03:31,226 --> 01:03:33,592
I thought you thought I was different.

1034
01:03:34,063 --> 01:03:35,360
I thought...

1035
01:03:35,463 --> 01:03:36,623
(SNORING)

1036
01:03:39,068 --> 01:03:40,592
I didn't have to help you!

1037
01:03:40,702 --> 01:03:44,036
If I looked out only for myself,
I would have let you drown!

1038
01:03:44,139 --> 01:03:45,231
But...

1039
01:03:46,141 --> 01:03:50,737
I wanted you to succeed. I liked you.

1040
01:03:52,715 --> 01:03:54,012
My mistake.

1041
01:03:54,750 --> 01:03:58,048
Colette. Wait, wait. Colette!

1042
01:03:58,253 --> 01:04:01,188
It's over, Little Chef.
I can't do it anymore.

1043
01:04:01,556 --> 01:04:05,253
Colette! Wait, wait!
Don't motorcycle away.

1044
01:04:05,360 --> 01:04:08,693
Look, I'm no good with words.
I'm no good with food either.

1045
01:04:08,797 --> 01:04:10,525
At least not without your help.

1046
01:04:10,632 --> 01:04:14,034
I hate false modesty.
It's just another way to lie.

1047
01:04:14,503 --> 01:04:18,302
- (SIGHS) You have talent.
- No, but I don't! Really! It's not me.

1048
01:04:18,773 --> 01:04:20,503
When I added that extra ingredient

1049
01:04:20,608 --> 01:04:23,442
instead of following the recipe
like you said,

1050
01:04:23,545 --> 01:04:25,739
(CHUCKLING)
that wasn't me either.

1051
01:04:25,847 --> 01:04:28,748
- What do you mean?
- I mean, I wouldn't have done that.

1052
01:04:28,851 --> 01:04:30,648
I would've followed the recipe.

1053
01:04:30,753 --> 01:04:32,117
I would've followed your advice.

1054
01:04:32,221 --> 01:04:34,052
I would've followed your advice
to the ends of the earth.

1055
01:04:34,155 --> 01:04:38,320
- Because I love your advice.
- But...

1056
01:04:38,427 --> 01:04:40,088
But I...

1057
01:04:40,461 --> 01:04:41,759
Don't do it.

1058
01:04:41,864 --> 01:04:45,163
I have a secret. It's sort of disturbing.

1059
01:04:45,434 --> 01:04:46,695
(TITTERING)

1060
01:04:47,536 --> 01:04:50,436
- I have a...
- (STUTTERING) What? You...

1061
01:04:50,539 --> 01:04:54,737
- I have a ra...
- You have a rash?

1062
01:04:54,876 --> 01:05:00,143
No, no, no. I have this...
This tiny little...

1063
01:05:00,349 --> 01:05:01,509
Little...

1064
01:05:02,550 --> 01:05:04,711
(SPEAKING QUICKLY) A tiny chef
who tells me what to do.

1065
01:05:04,820 --> 01:05:06,811
(IN DISBELIEF) A tiny chef?

1066
01:05:06,922 --> 01:05:09,447
Yes. Yes. He's...

1067
01:05:11,293 --> 01:05:14,420
- He's up here.
- In your brain?

1068
01:05:14,996 --> 01:05:16,021
(GRUNTING)

1069
01:05:16,130 --> 01:05:19,896
Why is it so hard to talk to you?
Okay. Here we go.

1070
01:05:21,036 --> 01:05:24,938
You inspire me. I'm going to risk it all.

1071
01:05:25,139 --> 01:05:29,907
I'm going to risk looking like the
biggest idiot psycho you've ever seen.

1072
01:05:30,012 --> 01:05:32,206
You want to know why
I'm such a fast learner?

1073
01:05:32,313 --> 01:05:34,338
You want to know why
I'm such a great cook?

1074
01:05:34,449 --> 01:05:37,179
Don't laugh! I'm going to show you!

1075
01:05:40,722 --> 01:05:41,849
No! No!

1076
01:05:42,824 --> 01:05:43,985
(GRUNTING)

1077
01:06:12,688 --> 01:06:15,623
(TYPEWRITER CLICKING)

1078
01:06:27,101 --> 01:06:29,626
- What is it, Ambrister?
- Gusteau's.

1079
01:06:29,737 --> 01:06:32,639
- Finally closing, is it?
- No.

1080
01:06:32,740 --> 01:06:35,835
- More financial trouble?
- No, it's...

1081
01:06:35,943 --> 01:06:38,469
Announced a new line
of microwave egg rolls?

1082
01:06:38,579 --> 01:06:40,411
What? What? Spit it out.

1083
01:06:40,516 --> 01:06:43,952
(STUTTERING)
It's come back. It's popular.

1084
01:06:48,257 --> 01:06:51,885
- I haven't reviewed Gusteau's in years.
- No, sir.

1085
01:06:51,994 --> 01:06:53,085
My last review condemned it

1086
01:06:53,195 --> 01:06:54,719
- to the tourist trade.
- Yes, sir.

1087
01:06:54,829 --> 01:06:59,027
I said, "Gusteau has finally
found his rightful place in history

1088
01:06:59,134 --> 01:07:02,900
"right alongside
another equally famous chef,

1089
01:07:03,005 --> 01:07:04,768
(IN DISGUST) "Monsieur Boyardee."

1090
01:07:04,873 --> 01:07:05,862
Touché.

1091
01:07:05,974 --> 01:07:09,340
That is where I left it.
That was my last word.

1092
01:07:09,510 --> 01:07:12,480
- The last word.
- Yes.

1093
01:07:12,581 --> 01:07:14,878
Then tell me, Ambrister,

1094
01:07:15,818 --> 01:07:19,753
how could it be popular?

1095
01:07:20,688 --> 01:07:25,251
No, no, no, no, no, no, no!

1096
01:07:25,360 --> 01:07:28,487
The DNA matches, the timing works,
everything checks out.

1097
01:07:28,597 --> 01:07:29,824
He is Gusteau's son.

1098
01:07:29,931 --> 01:07:33,833
This can't just happen!
The whole thing is a setup!

1099
01:07:33,936 --> 01:07:35,266
The boy knows!

1100
01:07:35,369 --> 01:07:38,362
Look at him out there,
pretending to be an idiot.

1101
01:07:38,474 --> 01:07:42,876
He's toying with my mind
like a cat with a ball of... Something.

1102
01:07:42,978 --> 01:07:45,411
- String?
- Yes! Playing dumb.

1103
01:07:45,514 --> 01:07:47,572
- Taunting me with that rat.
- Rat?

1104
01:07:47,682 --> 01:07:49,378
Yes. He's consorting with it.

1105
01:07:49,485 --> 01:07:52,010
Deliberately trying to make me think
it's important.

1106
01:07:52,121 --> 01:07:54,612
- The rat.
- Exactly!

1107
01:07:55,923 --> 01:07:58,518
Is the rat important?

1108
01:07:58,760 --> 01:08:01,990
Of course not!
He just wants me to think that it is.

1109
01:08:02,097 --> 01:08:04,360
Oh, I see the theatricality of it.

1110
01:08:04,465 --> 01:08:07,128
A rat appears on the boy's first night,
I order him to kill it.

1111
01:08:07,235 --> 01:08:09,760
And now he wants me
to see it everywhere.

1112
01:08:09,871 --> 01:08:11,702
(EX CITEDLY) Ooh!

1113
01:08:11,806 --> 01:08:13,865
It's here! No, it isn't, it's here!

1114
01:08:13,976 --> 01:08:17,207
Am I seeing things, am I crazy?
Is there a phantom rat or is there not?

1115
01:08:17,311 --> 01:08:18,404
But, oh, no!

1116
01:08:18,514 --> 01:08:22,712
I refuse to be sucked into
his little game of...

1117
01:08:25,921 --> 01:08:31,416
Should I be concerned about this?
About you?

1118
01:08:37,533 --> 01:08:38,500
(SIGHING)

1119
01:08:38,600 --> 01:08:39,567
Huh?

1120
01:08:51,345 --> 01:08:53,246
I can't fire him. He's getting attention.

1121
01:08:53,347 --> 01:08:55,713
If I fire him now,
everyone will wonder why.

1122
01:08:55,817 --> 01:08:58,284
And the last thing I want
is people looking into this.

1123
01:08:58,386 --> 01:09:00,014
What are you so worried about?

1124
01:09:00,122 --> 01:09:01,350
Isn't it good to have the press?

1125
01:09:01,456 --> 01:09:04,083
Isn't it good to have Gusteau's name
getting headlines?

1126
01:09:04,193 --> 01:09:06,592
Not if they're over his face!

1127
01:09:07,128 --> 01:09:10,792
Gusteau's already has a face,
and it's fat and lovable and familiar.

1128
01:09:10,899 --> 01:09:15,859
And it sells burritos!
Millions and millions of burritos!

1129
01:09:15,970 --> 01:09:17,939
The deadline passes in three days.

1130
01:09:18,039 --> 01:09:20,975
Then you can fire him
whenever he ceases to be valuable

1131
01:09:21,076 --> 01:09:23,203
and no one will ever know.

1132
01:09:23,744 --> 01:09:26,179
I was worried
about the hair sample you gave me.

1133
01:09:26,280 --> 01:09:28,715
- I had to send them back to the lab.
- Why?

1134
01:09:28,817 --> 01:09:33,345
Because the first time it came back
identified as rodent hair.

1135
01:09:39,060 --> 01:09:40,288
- No, no, no.
- LINGUINl: What?

1136
01:09:40,395 --> 01:09:42,693
Try this. It's better.

1137
01:09:49,805 --> 01:09:51,238
(GRUNTING)

1138
01:09:53,307 --> 01:09:54,832
(SIGHING)

1139
01:09:56,778 --> 01:09:58,904
Well, because you...

1140
01:09:59,981 --> 01:10:00,970
Whoa!

1141
01:10:01,082 --> 01:10:02,481
(BOTH LAUGHING)

1142
01:10:09,957 --> 01:10:11,618
(LINGUINI LAUGHING)

1143
01:10:14,863 --> 01:10:16,091
(GASPING)

1144
01:10:21,502 --> 01:10:23,060
(PEOPLE CHATTERING)

1145
01:10:23,171 --> 01:10:24,137
Rat!

1146
01:10:24,238 --> 01:10:25,706
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

1147
01:10:30,679 --> 01:10:32,908
WOMAN: Disgusting little creatures.

1148
01:10:42,791 --> 01:10:45,725
REMY: I was reminded
how fragile it all was.

1149
01:10:46,627 --> 01:10:48,755
How the world really saw me.

1150
01:10:50,298 --> 01:10:53,529
And it just kept getting better.

1151
01:10:54,036 --> 01:10:54,269
EMILE: Remy!

1152
01:10:54,269 --> 01:10:55,201
EMILE: Remy!

1153
01:10:55,304 --> 01:10:56,565
Psst! Psst!

1154
01:10:58,739 --> 01:11:01,140
Hey, hey, hey, little brother!

1155
01:11:01,342 --> 01:11:04,869
We were afraid you weren't going to,
you know, show up.

1156
01:11:05,079 --> 01:11:08,880
- Hey, Remy! How you doing?
- You told them?

1157
01:11:08,984 --> 01:11:11,850
Emile,
that's exactly what I said not to do!

1158
01:11:11,953 --> 01:11:13,716
But you know these guys.
They're my friends.

1159
01:11:13,822 --> 01:11:14,913
I didn't think you meant them.

1160
01:11:15,023 --> 01:11:17,115
(GROANING) Look, I'm sorry.

1161
01:11:17,225 --> 01:11:19,693
Don't tell me you're sorry,
tell them you're sorry.

1162
01:11:19,795 --> 01:11:24,356
- Is there a problem over here?
- No, there is not.

1163
01:11:24,466 --> 01:11:25,762
Wait here.

1164
01:11:31,640 --> 01:11:32,902
It's locked?

1165
01:11:34,342 --> 01:11:35,332
Hmm...

1166
01:11:39,948 --> 01:11:41,744
Remy, what are you doing in here?

1167
01:11:41,850 --> 01:11:44,648
Okay. Emile shows up with...

1168
01:11:44,752 --> 01:11:48,689
Okay, I said not to. I told him...
He goes and blabs to...

1169
01:11:48,890 --> 01:11:50,948
Yeah, it's a disaster.

1170
01:11:51,059 --> 01:11:54,688
Anyway, they're hungry, the food safe
is locked and I need the key.

1171
01:11:54,796 --> 01:11:58,699
- They want you to steal food?
- Yes. No! It's...

1172
01:11:58,699 --> 01:11:58,994
- They want you to steal food?
- Yes. No! It's...

1173
01:11:59,100 --> 01:12:02,900
It's complicated. It's family.
They don't have your ideals.

1174
01:12:03,003 --> 01:12:05,631
(IN SOUTHERN ACCENT) Ideals?
If Chef Fancy Pants had any ideals,

1175
01:12:05,740 --> 01:12:07,800
you think I'd be hawking barbecue
over here?

1176
01:12:07,908 --> 01:12:08,966
(IN MEXICAN ACCENT)
Or microwave burritos?

1177
01:12:09,077 --> 01:12:11,136
Or, Tooth, I say,
Tooth Pick'n Chicken?

1178
01:12:11,246 --> 01:12:13,009
About as French as a corn dog!

1179
01:12:13,215 --> 01:12:14,238
(BARKING) Coming soon!

1180
01:12:14,349 --> 01:12:16,248
We're inventing new ways
to sell out over here.

1181
01:12:16,350 --> 01:12:17,943
(IN SCOTTISH ACCENT)
Will ye be wanting some haggis bites?

1182
01:12:18,052 --> 01:12:19,713
I cannot control
how they use my image, Remy.

1183
01:12:19,820 --> 01:12:22,220
- I am dead!
- Can you guys shut up?

1184
01:12:23,291 --> 01:12:27,351
I've got to think! Word's getting out.
If I can't keep them quiet,

1185
01:12:27,462 --> 01:12:30,726
the entire clan's gonna be after me
with their mouths open and...

1186
01:12:30,832 --> 01:12:31,855
Here it is.

1187
01:12:32,300 --> 01:12:34,597
Hey. Your will!

1188
01:12:34,703 --> 01:12:39,332
- Oh, this is interesting. Mind if I...
- Not at all.

1189
01:12:42,010 --> 01:12:43,375
Linguini?

1190
01:12:44,212 --> 01:12:46,942
Why would Linguini be filed
with your will?

1191
01:12:47,047 --> 01:12:48,878
This used to be my office.

1192
01:13:12,173 --> 01:13:13,640
He's your son?

1193
01:13:13,742 --> 01:13:16,609
- I have a son?
- How could you not know this?

1194
01:13:16,711 --> 01:13:20,703
I am a figment of your imagination.
You did not know, how could I?

1195
01:13:20,815 --> 01:13:21,615
Well, your son is the rightful owner
of this restaurant!

1196
01:13:21,615 --> 01:13:24,516
Well, your son is the rightful owner
of this restaurant!

1197
01:13:24,819 --> 01:13:25,809
(GASPING)

1198
01:13:25,921 --> 01:13:27,588
No! No! The rat!

1199
01:13:28,055 --> 01:13:29,250
(GROANING)

1200
01:13:31,126 --> 01:13:32,490
(SCREAMING)

1201
01:13:33,662 --> 01:13:36,460
- Sorry, chef.
- The rat! It's stolen my documents!

1202
01:13:36,564 --> 01:13:38,930
- It's getting away!
- LALO: Hey, Mr. Chef!

1203
01:13:50,377 --> 01:13:51,640
(HORN BLARING)

1204
01:14:01,389 --> 01:14:02,650
(SCREAMING)

1205
01:14:29,618 --> 01:14:30,880
(GRUNTS)

1206
01:14:54,442 --> 01:14:55,601
(SCREAMING)

1207
01:15:04,351 --> 01:15:05,682
(GROANS)

1208
01:15:12,127 --> 01:15:13,150
(LAUGHING)

1209
01:15:13,261 --> 01:15:14,853
(GASPS) You!

1210
01:15:14,962 --> 01:15:19,627
- Get out of my office.
- He's not in your office. You are in his.

1211
01:15:22,871 --> 01:15:24,838
Bottoms up, Linguini!

1212
01:15:24,939 --> 01:15:27,340
(LE FES TIN PLAYING)

1213
01:15:27,442 --> 01:15:28,703
HORST: Cheers, ja.

1214
01:15:36,451 --> 01:15:38,385
(ALL CHUCKLING)

1215
01:15:44,091 --> 01:15:45,393
(GRUMBLING)

1216
01:16:21,695 --> 01:16:23,095
(HORST EX CLAIMING
ANGRILY)

1217
01:16:35,944 --> 01:16:38,242
REPORTER 1: Chef! Chef!
REPORTER 2: Chef Linguini!

1218
01:16:38,345 --> 01:16:39,335
(REPORTERS CLAMORING)

1219
01:16:39,447 --> 01:16:42,506
Your rise has been meteoric,
yet you have no formal training.

1220
01:16:42,617 --> 01:16:44,050
What is the secret to your genius?

1221
01:16:44,152 --> 01:16:47,747
LINGUINl: Secret? You want the truth?

1222
01:16:48,422 --> 01:16:53,884
(HESITANTLY) I am Gusteau's son.
It's in my blood I guess.

1223
01:16:53,994 --> 01:16:56,327
FEMALE REPORTER: But you weren't
aware of that fact until very recently.

1224
01:16:56,430 --> 01:16:57,398
No.

1225
01:16:57,498 --> 01:17:00,262
MALE REPORTER: And it resulted in
your taking ownership of this restaurant.

1226
01:17:00,368 --> 01:17:01,858
How did you find out?

1227
01:17:01,970 --> 01:17:05,234
Well, some part of me just knew.

1228
01:17:05,774 --> 01:17:07,104
The Gusteau part?

1229
01:17:08,510 --> 01:17:13,140
- Where do you get your inspiration?
- Inspiration has many names.

1230
01:17:13,347 --> 01:17:15,975
- Mine is named Colette.
- What?

1231
01:17:16,283 --> 01:17:17,478
(REMY SQUEAKING)

1232
01:17:17,585 --> 01:17:19,644
Something's stuck in my teeth.

1233
01:17:19,887 --> 01:17:21,082
(RINGING)

1234
01:17:23,158 --> 01:17:24,454
Health Inspector.

1235
01:17:24,559 --> 01:17:27,186
I wish to report a rat infestation.

1236
01:17:27,395 --> 01:17:28,487
It's taken over my...

1237
01:17:28,595 --> 01:17:30,962
(STAMMERING) Gusteau's restaurant.

1238
01:17:31,065 --> 01:17:32,123
Gusteau's, eh?

1239
01:17:32,266 --> 01:17:36,430
I can drop by. Let's see.
First opening is three months.

1240
01:17:36,537 --> 01:17:38,631
It must happen now!
It's a gourmet restaurant!

1241
01:17:38,739 --> 01:17:41,606
Monsieur, I have the information.
If someone cancels, I'll slot you in.

1242
01:17:41,710 --> 01:17:43,802
(STAMMERING) But the rat!
You must...

1243
01:17:43,912 --> 01:17:45,378
(DIAL TONE DRONING)

1244
01:17:45,479 --> 01:17:47,380
It stole my documents.

1245
01:17:48,582 --> 01:17:50,140
It's past opening time.

1246
01:17:50,251 --> 01:17:52,685
(GROANING) He should have
finished an hour ago.

1247
01:17:53,287 --> 01:17:54,481
(LAUGHING)

1248
01:17:54,588 --> 01:17:56,819
Bonjour, ma chérie.
Join us.

1249
01:17:56,925 --> 01:17:59,051
We were just talking
about my inspiration.

1250
01:17:59,260 --> 01:18:01,557
Yes, he calls it his tiny chef.

1251
01:18:01,662 --> 01:18:02,720
(SQUEAKING)

1252
01:18:02,831 --> 01:18:05,230
Not that, dearest. I meant you.

1253
01:18:05,332 --> 01:18:06,560
(DOOR OPENING)

1254
01:18:06,667 --> 01:18:07,760
(REPORTERS GASPING)

1255
01:18:07,868 --> 01:18:09,597
- It's him.
- Ego?

1256
01:18:09,703 --> 01:18:10,671
Anton Ego!

1257
01:18:10,872 --> 01:18:12,134
REPORTER: Is that Ego?

1258
01:18:12,907 --> 01:18:14,340
I can't believe it.

1259
01:18:14,509 --> 01:18:17,774
- You are Monsieur Linguini?
- Hello.

1260
01:18:17,878 --> 01:18:22,372
Pardon me for interrupting
your premature celebration,

1261
01:18:22,484 --> 01:18:26,180
but I thought it only fair
to give you a sporting chance

1262
01:18:26,287 --> 01:18:28,448
as you are new to this game.

1263
01:18:29,724 --> 01:18:30,985
- Game?
- Yes.

1264
01:18:31,091 --> 01:18:34,152
And you've been playing
without an opponent.

1265
01:18:34,261 --> 01:18:39,393
Which is, as you may have guessed,
against the rules.

1266
01:18:39,600 --> 01:18:41,659
You're Anton Ego.

1267
01:18:41,802 --> 01:18:43,134
(CHUCKLING)

1268
01:18:43,238 --> 01:18:46,139
You're slow
for someone in the fast lane.

1269
01:18:46,240 --> 01:18:47,640
(PEOPLE GASPING)

1270
01:18:47,742 --> 01:18:50,711
And you're thin
for someone who likes food.

1271
01:18:50,811 --> 01:18:52,279
(ALL GASPING IN SHOCK)

1272
01:18:54,314 --> 01:18:58,341
I don't like food. I love it.

1273
01:18:58,787 --> 01:19:03,019
If I don't love it, I don't swallow.

1274
01:19:03,123 --> 01:19:04,283
(GULPING)

1275
01:19:04,391 --> 01:19:08,350
I will return tomorrow night
with high expectations.

1276
01:19:08,796 --> 01:19:11,595
Pray you don't disappoint me.

1277
01:19:13,935 --> 01:19:15,663
(REPORTERS MURMURING)

1278
01:19:18,907 --> 01:19:22,342
Listen, we hate to be rude,
but we're French, and it's dinnertime.

1279
01:19:22,443 --> 01:19:25,570
She meant to say,
"It's dinnertime and we're French."

1280
01:19:27,448 --> 01:19:29,006
Don't give me that look.

1281
01:19:29,117 --> 01:19:31,278
You were distracting me
in front of the press.

1282
01:19:31,386 --> 01:19:35,823
How am I supposed to concentrate with
you yanking on my hair all the time?

1283
01:19:35,923 --> 01:19:37,185
And that's another thing.

1284
01:19:37,292 --> 01:19:40,193
Your opinion isn't the only one
that matters here.

1285
01:19:40,295 --> 01:19:42,889
Colette knows how to cook, too,
you know.

1286
01:19:42,997 --> 01:19:44,487
All right, that's it!

1287
01:19:48,603 --> 01:19:50,332
You take a break, Little Chef.

1288
01:19:50,438 --> 01:19:51,666
I'm not your puppet,

1289
01:19:51,773 --> 01:19:54,867
and you're not
my puppet-controlling guy!

1290
01:19:54,975 --> 01:19:56,773
(GASPS) The rat is the cook.

1291
01:19:56,877 --> 01:19:57,511
You cool off and get your mind right,
Little Chef.

1292
01:19:57,511 --> 01:19:59,775
You cool off and get your mind right,
Little Chef.

1293
01:19:59,881 --> 01:20:02,850
Ego is coming, and I need to focus!

1294
01:20:04,719 --> 01:20:05,845
(GRUNTING)

1295
01:20:05,953 --> 01:20:07,319
You stupid...

1296
01:20:07,421 --> 01:20:09,753
(GRUMBLING ANGRILY)

1297
01:20:09,858 --> 01:20:13,088
Wow. I have never seen that before.

1298
01:20:13,194 --> 01:20:16,493
Yeah, it's like you're his fluffy bunny
or something.

1299
01:20:16,597 --> 01:20:17,895
(RATS LAUGHING)

1300
01:20:17,998 --> 01:20:19,488
EMILE: I'm sorry, Remy.

1301
01:20:19,600 --> 01:20:20,590
I know there are too many guys.

1302
01:20:20,702 --> 01:20:21,668
- I tried to limit...
- You know what?

1303
01:20:21,769 --> 01:20:23,600
It's okay. I've been selfish.

1304
01:20:23,704 --> 01:20:25,729
- You guys hungry?
- Are you kidding?

1305
01:20:25,840 --> 01:20:28,809
All right. Dinner's on me.
We'll go after closing time.

1306
01:20:28,909 --> 01:20:30,069
- In fact...
- Yeah.

1307
01:20:30,177 --> 01:20:32,543
...tell Dad to bring the whole clan.

1308
01:20:34,181 --> 01:20:35,706
Little Chef?

1309
01:20:45,193 --> 01:20:49,926
This is great, Son.
An inside job. I see the appeal.

1310
01:20:50,030 --> 01:20:51,395
(SHUSHING)

1311
01:20:57,104 --> 01:20:58,595
(CLICKS TONGUE)

1312
01:21:09,583 --> 01:21:10,641
Oof!

1313
01:21:10,752 --> 01:21:11,810
(BECKONS)

1314
01:21:20,360 --> 01:21:21,885
(KE YS JINGLING)

1315
01:21:21,996 --> 01:21:23,189
(ALL GASP)

1316
01:21:26,868 --> 01:21:28,266
Little Chef?

1317
01:21:29,037 --> 01:21:30,298
Little Chef?

1318
01:21:31,038 --> 01:21:32,631
Hey, Little Chef.

1319
01:21:32,974 --> 01:21:36,033
I thought you went back
to the apartment.

1320
01:21:36,243 --> 01:21:40,373
Then when you weren't there,
I don't know...

1321
01:21:40,715 --> 01:21:44,742
It didn't seem right to leave things
the way that we did, so...

1322
01:21:45,787 --> 01:21:47,686
Look, I don't want to fight.

1323
01:21:47,889 --> 01:21:50,516
I've been under a lot of, you know,
pressure.

1324
01:21:50,725 --> 01:21:54,057
A lot has changed
in not very much time, you know?

1325
01:21:54,162 --> 01:21:55,423
I'm suddenly a Gusteau.

1326
01:21:55,529 --> 01:21:57,430
And I got to be a Gusteau or, you know,

1327
01:21:58,699 --> 01:22:00,257
people will be disappointed.

1328
01:22:00,667 --> 01:22:02,260
It's weird.

1329
01:22:02,369 --> 01:22:05,305
You know, I've never
disappointed anyone before,

1330
01:22:05,405 --> 01:22:08,203
because nobody's
ever expected anything of me.

1331
01:22:08,309 --> 01:22:11,073
And the only reason
anyone expects anything from me now

1332
01:22:11,179 --> 01:22:13,340
is because of you.

1333
01:22:14,983 --> 01:22:16,677
I haven't been fair to you.

1334
01:22:16,783 --> 01:22:20,242
You've never failed me,
and I should never forget that.

1335
01:22:20,454 --> 01:22:22,149
You've been a good friend.

1336
01:22:22,356 --> 01:22:25,382
The most honorable friend
a guy could ever ask...

1337
01:22:25,493 --> 01:22:26,585
(GROANS)

1338
01:22:27,328 --> 01:22:28,625
What is this?

1339
01:22:29,096 --> 01:22:30,792
What's going on?

1340
01:22:33,234 --> 01:22:34,222
What...

1341
01:22:34,335 --> 01:22:35,301
Hey...

1342
01:22:35,903 --> 01:22:37,199
(STUTTERING) You're...

1343
01:22:37,305 --> 01:22:40,364
You're stealing food? How could you?

1344
01:22:40,475 --> 01:22:43,603
I thought you were my friend!
I trusted you!

1345
01:22:43,810 --> 01:22:46,041
Get out! You and all your rat buddies!

1346
01:22:46,146 --> 01:22:47,546
And don't come back

1347
01:22:47,648 --> 01:22:51,105
or I'll treat you the way restaurants
are supposed to treat pests!

1348
01:22:59,226 --> 01:23:02,492
You're right, Dad. Who am I kidding?

1349
01:23:03,030 --> 01:23:06,431
We are what we are, and we're rats.

1350
01:23:07,902 --> 01:23:11,702
Well, he'll leave soon,
and now you know how to get in.

1351
01:23:12,172 --> 01:23:13,572
Steal all you want.

1352
01:23:13,673 --> 01:23:16,609
- You're not coming?
- I've lost my appetite.

1353
01:23:31,192 --> 01:23:33,659
Do you know
what you would like this evening, sir?

1354
01:23:33,761 --> 01:23:38,561
Yes,
I'd like your heart roasted on a spit.

1355
01:23:38,865 --> 01:23:40,457
(ANTON SNICKERING)

1356
01:23:40,568 --> 01:23:41,626
(AN TON SNICKERIN G)

1357
01:23:41,735 --> 01:23:42,703
(EX CLAIMS)

1358
01:23:42,804 --> 01:23:43,828
(KNOCKING ON DOOR)

1359
01:23:43,938 --> 01:23:45,496
Come in!

1360
01:23:45,706 --> 01:23:48,903
Today's the big day.
You should say something to them.

1361
01:23:49,010 --> 01:23:52,877
- Like what?
- You are the boss. Inspire them.

1362
01:23:56,216 --> 01:23:57,707
(MEEKLY) Attention.

1363
01:23:57,819 --> 01:24:00,587
(MORE CONFIDENTLY)
Attention, everyone.

1364
01:24:00,755 --> 01:24:02,984
Tonight is a big night.

1365
01:24:03,190 --> 01:24:07,059
Appetite is coming,
and he's going to have a big ego.

1366
01:24:07,261 --> 01:24:11,220
I mean, Ego. He's coming. The critic.

1367
01:24:11,932 --> 01:24:14,902
And he's going to order something.

1368
01:24:15,502 --> 01:24:17,528
Something from our menu.

1369
01:24:18,238 --> 01:24:22,335
And we'll have to cook it,
unless he orders something cold.

1370
01:24:22,443 --> 01:24:24,307
EMILE: Just can't leave it alone,
can you?

1371
01:24:24,412 --> 01:24:28,041
You really shouldn't be here
during restaurant hours. It's not safe.

1372
01:24:28,149 --> 01:24:29,377
I'm hungry!

1373
01:24:29,484 --> 01:24:32,112
And I don't need the inside food
to be happy.

1374
01:24:32,220 --> 01:24:35,279
The key, my friend, is to not be picky.

1375
01:24:35,655 --> 01:24:37,715
- Observe.
- No, wait!

1376
01:24:39,359 --> 01:24:43,228
- Oh, no! No, no! What do we do?
- (STUTTERING) I'll go get Dad.

1377
01:24:43,430 --> 01:24:45,694
(SNICKERING)

1378
01:24:45,800 --> 01:24:52,069
You might think you are a chef
but you are still only a rat.

1379
01:24:52,472 --> 01:24:55,703
Sure he took away a star
last time he reviewed this place.

1380
01:24:55,810 --> 01:24:58,210
Sure it probably killed... Dad.

1381
01:24:58,512 --> 01:25:02,279
- This is very bad juju right here.
- But I'll tell you one thing...

1382
01:25:02,382 --> 01:25:05,113
- Ego is here.
- Ego? He is here?

1383
01:25:07,121 --> 01:25:11,284
Anton Ego is just another customer.
Let's cook!

1384
01:25:11,391 --> 01:25:13,256
Yeah! Let's...

1385
01:25:13,694 --> 01:25:14,887
Okay.

1386
01:25:16,363 --> 01:25:19,230
So I have in mind
a simple arrangement.

1387
01:25:19,432 --> 01:25:23,493
You will create for me a new line
of Chef Skinner frozen foods.

1388
01:25:23,604 --> 01:25:27,369
And I, in return, will not kill you.

1389
01:25:27,942 --> 01:25:29,466
(SNICKERING)

1390
01:25:31,145 --> 01:25:34,307
Au revoir, rat!

1391
01:25:36,716 --> 01:25:37,877
(SIGHS)

1392
01:25:41,521 --> 01:25:44,184
Do you know
what you would like this evening, sir?

1393
01:25:44,292 --> 01:25:45,815
Yes, I think I do.

1394
01:25:46,327 --> 01:25:50,457
After reading a lot of overheated
puffery about your new cook,

1395
01:25:50,564 --> 01:25:52,623
you know what I'm craving?

1396
01:25:53,701 --> 01:25:56,966
A little perspective.

1397
01:25:57,171 --> 01:26:02,234
That's it. I'd like some fresh, clear,
well seasoned perspective.

1398
01:26:02,342 --> 01:26:05,140
Can you suggest
a good wine to go with that?

1399
01:26:05,246 --> 01:26:10,149
- With what, sir?
- Perspective. Fresh out, I take it?

1400
01:26:10,251 --> 01:26:11,411
I am...

1401
01:26:12,552 --> 01:26:15,317
Very well.
Since you're all out of perspective

1402
01:26:15,422 --> 01:26:18,789
and no one else
seems to have it in this bloody town,

1403
01:26:18,893 --> 01:26:20,417
I'll make you a deal.

1404
01:26:20,528 --> 01:26:24,623
You provide the food,
I'll provide the perspective.

1405
01:26:24,731 --> 01:26:28,759
Which would go nicely
with a bottle of Cheval Blanc 1947.

1406
01:26:28,868 --> 01:26:30,666
I'm afraid I...

1407
01:26:32,372 --> 01:26:34,738
Your dinner selection?

1408
01:26:35,443 --> 01:26:40,210
Tell your Chef Linguini that I want
whatever he dares to serve me.

1409
01:26:40,314 --> 01:26:43,771
Tell him to hit me with his best shot.

1410
01:26:47,520 --> 01:26:50,421
I will have whatever he is having.

1411
01:26:57,265 --> 01:27:00,756
- So, we have given up.
- Why do you say that?

1412
01:27:00,967 --> 01:27:03,993
We are in a cage inside the car trunk

1413
01:27:04,204 --> 01:27:07,105
awaiting a future
in frozen food products.

1414
01:27:07,307 --> 01:27:11,073
No, I'm the one in a cage. I've given up.

1415
01:27:11,412 --> 01:27:13,778
You are free.

1416
01:27:13,980 --> 01:27:17,381
I am only as free
as you imagine me to be.

1417
01:27:17,484 --> 01:27:18,712
As you are.

1418
01:27:18,819 --> 01:27:23,448
Oh, please. I'm sick of pretending.
I pretend to be a rat for my father.

1419
01:27:23,556 --> 01:27:25,957
I pretend to be a human
through Linguini.

1420
01:27:26,060 --> 01:27:28,789
I pretend you exist
so I have someone to talk to!

1421
01:27:28,895 --> 01:27:30,863
You only tell me stuff I already know!

1422
01:27:30,965 --> 01:27:33,957
I know who I am!
Why do I need you to tell me?

1423
01:27:34,068 --> 01:27:36,036
Why do I need to pretend?

1424
01:27:36,136 --> 01:27:37,434
(CHUCKLING)

1425
01:27:38,139 --> 01:27:39,765
But you don't, Remy.

1426
01:27:40,573 --> 01:27:42,201
You never did.

1427
01:27:48,649 --> 01:27:50,047
(CRASHING)

1428
01:27:51,185 --> 01:27:53,153
No. My other left!

1429
01:27:53,354 --> 01:27:55,150
REMY: (MUFFLED)
Dad? Dad, I'm in here!

1430
01:27:55,355 --> 01:27:57,654
I'm inside the trunk! What the...

1431
01:27:57,957 --> 01:27:58,947
Dad!

1432
01:27:59,592 --> 01:28:02,118
- Hey, little brother!
- Emile!

1433
01:28:05,666 --> 01:28:07,725
I love you guys!

1434
01:28:09,804 --> 01:28:10,862
Where are you going?

1435
01:28:10,970 --> 01:28:13,496
Back to the restaurant.
They'll fail without me.

1436
01:28:13,606 --> 01:28:17,167
- Why do you care?
- Because I'm a cook!

1437
01:28:19,546 --> 01:28:21,070
(STAFF CLAMORING)

1438
01:28:24,885 --> 01:28:26,681
It's your recipe.

1439
01:28:26,787 --> 01:28:28,845
How can you not know
your own recipe?

1440
01:28:28,956 --> 01:28:31,890
I didn't write it down. It just came to me.

1441
01:28:31,992 --> 01:28:35,086
Then make it come to you again, ja?
Because we can't serve this!

1442
01:28:35,195 --> 01:28:36,162
Where's my order?

1443
01:28:36,262 --> 01:28:38,628
Can't we serve something else?
Something I didn't invent?

1444
01:28:38,733 --> 01:28:39,791
This is what they're ordering.

1445
01:28:39,899 --> 01:28:42,231
Make them order something else.
Tell them we're all out.

1446
01:28:42,336 --> 01:28:44,030
We cannot be all out. We just opened.

1447
01:28:44,137 --> 01:28:47,130
I have another idea.
What if we serve them what they order!

1448
01:28:47,240 --> 01:28:49,368
We will make it.
Just tell us what you did.

1449
01:28:49,476 --> 01:28:50,841
I don't know what I did.

1450
01:28:50,944 --> 01:28:52,673
We need to tell
the customers something.

1451
01:28:52,779 --> 01:28:54,680
Then tell them... Tell them...

1452
01:28:54,782 --> 01:28:56,408
(SCREAMING)

1453
01:28:58,719 --> 01:28:59,980
Huh?

1454
01:29:00,787 --> 01:29:03,119
- Don't do it.
- Remy. Remy.

1455
01:29:03,224 --> 01:29:05,248
EMILE: Don't! Stop!
They'll see you. Stop.

1456
01:29:05,359 --> 01:29:09,363
We're not talking about me.
We're talking about what to do right...

1457
01:29:09,796 --> 01:29:10,764
Rats!

1458
01:29:12,533 --> 01:29:14,091
- Remy!
- Get my knife.

1459
01:29:14,568 --> 01:29:16,194
Don't touch him!

1460
01:29:18,506 --> 01:29:20,872
(WHISPERING)
Thanks for coming back, Little Chef.

1461
01:29:22,176 --> 01:29:24,474
I know this sounds insane, but...

1462
01:29:24,578 --> 01:29:27,137
Well,
the truth sounds insane sometimes.

1463
01:29:27,247 --> 01:29:29,045
But that doesn't mean it's not

1464
01:29:29,149 --> 01:29:31,345
(STAMMERING) the truth.

1465
01:29:32,051 --> 01:29:36,283
And the truth is, I have no talent at all.

1466
01:29:37,056 --> 01:29:40,958
But this rat,
he's the one behind these recipes.

1467
01:29:41,060 --> 01:29:46,158
He's the cook. The real cook.
He's been hiding under my toque.

1468
01:29:46,500 --> 01:29:48,434
He's been controlling my actions.

1469
01:29:48,536 --> 01:29:49,797
(ALL GASPING)

1470
01:29:50,503 --> 01:29:54,064
He's the reason I can cook the food
that's exciting everyone.

1471
01:29:54,274 --> 01:29:57,368
The reason Ego is outside that door.

1472
01:29:57,610 --> 01:30:00,408
You've been giving me credit
for his gift.

1473
01:30:00,680 --> 01:30:02,273
I know it's a hard thing to believe.

1474
01:30:02,382 --> 01:30:05,351
But, hey, you believed I could cook,
right?

1475
01:30:05,453 --> 01:30:06,750
(CHUCKLES)

1476
01:30:07,087 --> 01:30:11,251
Look, this works.
It's crazy, but it works.

1477
01:30:11,725 --> 01:30:14,193
We can be
the greatest restaurant in Paris,

1478
01:30:14,295 --> 01:30:19,733
and this rat, this brilliant Little Chef,
can lead us there.

1479
01:30:20,467 --> 01:30:22,868
What do you say? You with me?

1480
01:30:57,371 --> 01:30:58,599
(SIGHS)

1481
01:31:05,613 --> 01:31:08,877
(MOTORC YCLE STARTING)

1482
01:31:08,983 --> 01:31:10,314
(GROANS)

1483
01:31:35,341 --> 01:31:36,434
(HORN BLARING)

1484
01:31:36,543 --> 01:31:37,976
(TIRES SKIDDING)

1485
01:31:53,726 --> 01:31:56,719
(HORNS HONKING)

1486
01:32:02,735 --> 01:32:03,895
(SIGHS)

1487
01:32:10,844 --> 01:32:11,810
Dad.

1488
01:32:15,916 --> 01:32:18,885
Dad, I don't know what to say.

1489
01:32:19,086 --> 01:32:23,113
I was wrong about your friend
and about you.

1490
01:32:23,524 --> 01:32:27,391
I don't want you to think
I'm choosing this over family.

1491
01:32:27,595 --> 01:32:30,359
I can't choose
between two halves of myself.

1492
01:32:30,463 --> 01:32:34,297
I'm not talking about cooking.
I'm talking about guts.

1493
01:32:35,002 --> 01:32:37,402
This really means that much to you?

1494
01:32:41,041 --> 01:32:42,337
(WHISTLES)

1495
01:32:42,443 --> 01:32:44,034
(ALL CHATTERING)

1496
01:32:45,412 --> 01:32:48,381
We're not cooks, but we are family.

1497
01:32:48,582 --> 01:32:51,573
You tell us what to do,
and we'll get it done.

1498
01:32:59,560 --> 01:33:03,189
- Stop that health inspector!
- Delta Team, go, go, go, go!

1499
01:33:03,396 --> 01:33:05,524
The rest of you stay and help Remy.

1500
01:33:07,768 --> 01:33:09,735
(ELECTRIC ENGINE WHIRRING)

1501
01:33:16,944 --> 01:33:18,171
(ENGINE STARTS)

1502
01:33:28,655 --> 01:33:30,490
Team three will be handling fish.
Team four, roasted items.

1503
01:33:30,490 --> 01:33:32,118
Team three will be handling fish.
Team four, roasted items.

1504
01:33:32,326 --> 01:33:37,764
Team five, grill. Team six, sauces.
Get to your stations. Let's go, go, go!

1505
01:33:38,064 --> 01:33:40,555
Those handling food
will walk on two legs.

1506
01:33:50,277 --> 01:33:52,244
We need someone to wait tables.

1507
01:34:07,528 --> 01:34:10,554
I'm sorry for any delay,
but we're a little short tonight.

1508
01:34:10,663 --> 01:34:12,927
Please, take all of the time you need.

1509
01:34:16,103 --> 01:34:18,697
He came in late one more time
and all of a sudden he...

1510
01:34:23,010 --> 01:34:25,341
REMY: Make sure that steak
is nice and tenderized.

1511
01:34:25,445 --> 01:34:27,778
Work it. Yeah. Stick and move.
Stick and move.

1512
01:34:27,881 --> 01:34:31,408
Easy with that sole meuničre.
Less salt. More butter.

1513
01:34:31,618 --> 01:34:33,518
Only use the mimolette cheese.

1514
01:34:33,654 --> 01:34:37,283
Whoa! Compose the salad
like you were painting a picture.

1515
01:34:37,490 --> 01:34:40,118
Not too much vinaigrette
on that salade composée.

1516
01:34:40,226 --> 01:34:43,320
Don't let that beurre blanc separate.
Keep whisking.

1517
01:34:43,497 --> 01:34:47,661
Gently poach the scallops.
Taste check. Spoons down.

1518
01:34:47,868 --> 01:34:50,199
Good. Too much salt. Good.

1519
01:34:50,404 --> 01:34:53,305
Don't boil the consommé,
it'll toughen the pheasant. Emile!

1520
01:34:53,407 --> 01:34:54,498
Sorry.

1521
01:34:58,112 --> 01:35:00,273
Colette, wait! Colette.

1522
01:35:00,713 --> 01:35:04,740
- You came back. Colette...
- Don't say a word.

1523
01:35:04,851 --> 01:35:06,409
If I think about it,
I might change my mind.

1524
01:35:06,520 --> 01:35:08,988
Just tell me what the rat wants to cook.

1525
01:35:12,091 --> 01:35:14,582
Ratatouille? It's a peasant dish.

1526
01:35:14,728 --> 01:35:17,697
Are you sure
you want to serve this to Ego?

1527
01:35:23,970 --> 01:35:25,164
(DISHWARE SHATTERING)

1528
01:35:25,506 --> 01:35:29,135
(MUFFLED EX CLAIMING)

1529
01:35:36,182 --> 01:35:38,047
What? I am making ratatouille.

1530
01:35:38,152 --> 01:35:39,118
(SCOFFS)

1531
01:35:39,219 --> 01:35:41,686
Well, how would you prepare it?

1532
01:36:13,720 --> 01:36:16,882
Ratatouille? They must be joking.

1533
01:36:19,259 --> 01:36:20,418
(WHIMPERS)

1534
01:36:33,006 --> 01:36:34,404
(SNIFFLING)

1535
01:36:51,925 --> 01:36:53,256
(THUDDIN G)

1536
01:37:02,970 --> 01:37:04,231
Mmm.

1537
01:37:07,774 --> 01:37:09,537
No, it can't be.

1538
01:37:10,143 --> 01:37:13,771
Who cooked the ratatouille?
I demand to know!

1539
01:37:14,046 --> 01:37:15,412
(GASPING)

1540
01:37:15,515 --> 01:37:16,708
(CLATTERING)

1541
01:37:17,650 --> 01:37:19,140
(MUFFLED GROANING)

1542
01:37:20,787 --> 01:37:22,413
I can't remember the last time

1543
01:37:22,521 --> 01:37:25,820
I asked a waiter
to give my compliments to the chef.

1544
01:37:26,792 --> 01:37:29,591
And now I find myself
in the extraordinary position

1545
01:37:29,695 --> 01:37:31,788
of having my waiter be the chef.

1546
01:37:31,998 --> 01:37:34,934
Thanks, but I'm just your waiter tonight.

1547
01:37:36,002 --> 01:37:38,470
Then who do I thank for the meal?

1548
01:37:39,338 --> 01:37:41,033
Excuse me a minute.

1549
01:37:45,412 --> 01:37:47,106
(MUFFLED ARGUING)

1550
01:37:52,051 --> 01:37:53,041
You must be the chef...

1551
01:37:53,153 --> 01:37:55,279
If you wish to meet the chef,
you will have to wait

1552
01:37:55,389 --> 01:37:57,448
until all the other customer have gone.

1553
01:37:59,493 --> 01:38:00,653
So be it.

1554
01:38:22,349 --> 01:38:24,873
REMY: At first, Ego thinks it's a joke.

1555
01:38:25,085 --> 01:38:31,024
But as Linguini explains,
Ego's smile disappears.

1556
01:38:31,158 --> 01:38:32,625
(RATS SQUEAKING)

1557
01:38:36,630 --> 01:38:40,690
He doesn't react
beyond asking an occasional question.

1558
01:38:41,234 --> 01:38:45,603
And when the story is done,
Ego stands, thanks us for the meal...

1559
01:38:45,706 --> 01:38:47,367
Thank you for the meal.

1560
01:38:47,474 --> 01:38:50,341
...and leaves without another word.

1561
01:38:52,612 --> 01:38:56,547
The following day his review appears.

1562
01:38:59,086 --> 01:39:03,181
E GO: In many ways,
the work of a critic is easy.

1563
01:39:03,390 --> 01:39:07,622
We risk very little,
yet enjoy a position over those

1564
01:39:07,728 --> 01:39:11,788
who offer up their work
and their selves to our judgment.

1565
01:39:12,032 --> 01:39:17,402
We thrive on negative criticism,
which is fun to write and to read.

1566
01:39:17,938 --> 01:39:24,467
But the bitter truth we critics must face
is that in the grand scheme of things,

1567
01:39:24,578 --> 01:39:28,570
the average piece of junk
is probably more meaningful

1568
01:39:28,681 --> 01:39:31,947
than our criticism designating it so.

1569
01:39:32,319 --> 01:39:36,448
But there are times
when a critic truly risks something

1570
01:39:36,555 --> 01:39:40,855
and that is in the discovery
and defense of the new.

1571
01:39:40,961 --> 01:39:45,556
The world is often unkind
to new talent, new creations.

1572
01:39:45,765 --> 01:39:48,234
The new needs friends.

1573
01:39:48,534 --> 01:39:52,061
Last night,
I experienced something new,

1574
01:39:52,271 --> 01:39:57,231
an extraordinary meal
from a singularly unexpected source.

1575
01:39:57,444 --> 01:40:00,072
To say that both the meal
and its maker

1576
01:40:00,180 --> 01:40:03,671
have challenged my preconceptions
about fine cooking

1577
01:40:03,783 --> 01:40:06,479
is a gross understatement.

1578
01:40:06,886 --> 01:40:10,083
They have rocked me to my core.

1579
01:40:10,823 --> 01:40:14,282
In the past, I have made no secret
of my disdain

1580
01:40:14,394 --> 01:40:19,354
for Chef Gusteau's famous motto,
"Anyone can cook."

1581
01:40:19,666 --> 01:40:25,865
But I realize only now
do I truly understand what he meant.

1582
01:40:26,172 --> 01:40:30,109
Not everyone
can become a great artist,

1583
01:40:30,210 --> 01:40:34,543
but a great artist
can come from anywhere.

1584
01:40:35,148 --> 01:40:38,412
It is difficult to imagine
more humble origins

1585
01:40:38,518 --> 01:40:42,386
than those of the genius
now cooking at Gusteau's,

1586
01:40:42,488 --> 01:40:45,322
who is, in this critic's opinion,

1587
01:40:45,425 --> 01:40:49,657
nothing less
than the finest chef in France.

1588
01:40:49,863 --> 01:40:51,730
I will be returning to Gusteau's soon,
hungry for more.

1589
01:40:51,730 --> 01:40:55,189
I will be returning to Gusteau's soon,
hungry for more.

1590
01:40:55,569 --> 01:40:57,092
REMY: It was a great night.

1591
01:40:57,203 --> 01:40:58,932
(CHUCKLIN G) The happiest of my life.

1592
01:40:59,038 --> 01:41:03,567
But the only thing predictable
about life is its unpredictability.

1593
01:41:03,676 --> 01:41:06,840
Well, we had to let Skinner
and the health inspector loose,

1594
01:41:06,947 --> 01:41:09,346
and of course they ratted us out.

1595
01:41:09,716 --> 01:41:11,342
The food didn't matter.

1596
01:41:11,451 --> 01:41:13,817
Once it got out
there were rats in the kitchen,

1597
01:41:13,920 --> 01:41:15,979
oh, man, the restaurant was closed

1598
01:41:16,088 --> 01:41:18,819
and Ego lost his job and his credibility.

1599
01:41:18,925 --> 01:41:20,859
But don't feel too bad for him.

1600
01:41:20,961 --> 01:41:24,453
He's doing very well
as a small business investor.

1601
01:41:24,797 --> 01:41:27,358
- He seems very happy.
- How do you know?

1602
01:41:31,872 --> 01:41:33,930
(LE FES TIN PLAYING)

1603
01:41:35,542 --> 01:41:37,668
Got to go. Dinner rush.

1604
01:41:45,252 --> 01:41:46,912
You know how he likes it.

1605
01:41:52,292 --> 01:41:53,884
Thanks, Little Chef.

1606
01:42:00,567 --> 01:42:03,399
Can I interest you
in a dessert this evening?

1607
01:42:03,502 --> 01:42:06,631
- Don't you always?
- Which one would you like?

1608
01:42:07,774 --> 01:42:09,604
Surprise me.

1609
01:42:15,015 --> 01:42:18,451
Can I interest you
in a dessert this evening?

1610
01:42:20,353 --> 01:42:21,819
(RATS CHUCKLING)

1611
01:42:21,921 --> 01:42:25,585
Hey, believe me, that story
gets better when I tell it, okay?

1612
01:42:27,493 --> 01:42:30,587
Come on. Bring some food over here,
we're starving!
